INTRODUCTION: Hip replacement was declared "operation of the century" in tribute 
to the functional improvement it provides. Frequency is increasing, but it is 
difficult to estimate the actual number of procedures performed and the expected 
progression, because of changes in indications and lengthening life-expectancy, 
and also, in France, because there is no registry. As data are lacking in 
